  <front>
    <title>Handling Unknown DHCPv6 Messages</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-ietf-dhc-dhcpv6-unknown-msg-04"/>
    <author initials="Y." surname="Cui" fullname="Yong Cui"/>
    <author initials="Q." surname="Sun" fullname="Qi Sun"/>
    <author initials="T." surname="Lemon" fullname="Ted Lemon"/>
    <date day="15" month="December" year="2013"></date>
    <abstract>
      <t>   DHCPv6 is not specific about handling messages with unknown types.
   This memo describes the problems and defines how a DHCPv6 server,
   client or relay agent should behave when receiving unknown DHCPv6
   messages.  This document updates RFC3315.

	 </t>
    </abstract>
